<bibRefCitation author="Loomis, H. F. &amp; R. L. Hoffman" box="[744,1035,1846,1868]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" pagination="145 - 158" refId="ref6135" refString="Loomis, H. F., and R. L. Hoffman. 1962. A remarkable new family of spined polydesmoid Diplopoda, including a species lacking gonopods in the male sex. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington 75: 145 - 158." type="journal article" year="1962">Loomis and Hoffman 1962</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Shear, W. A." box="[1043,1171,1846,1868]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" pagination="235 - 265" refId="ref6332" refString="Shear, W. A. 1977. Millipeds (Diplopoda) from caves in Mexico, Belize and Guatemala. III. Problemi attuali di scienza e di cultura di Accademia Nazionale dei Lincei 171 (3): 235 - 265." type="journal article" year="1977">Shear 1977</bibRefCitation>
). Red dot, type locality of 
